  <h2>2. Scope</h2>
  <p>This Policy describes how we collect, use, store, and share information when you use the {{ site.name }} mobile application and related websites (the “<strong>Services</strong>”).</p>

  <h2>3. Information we collect</h2>
  <h3>3.1 You provide</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account data:</strong> email address and authentication credentials (via Firebase Authentication). If enabled, profile data from <strong>Google</strong> or <strong>Facebook</strong> sign-in as permitted by those providers.</li>
    <li><strong>Planning inputs:</strong> home price targets, budget assumptions, income and debt information you enter, savings rates, timeline choices, credit/readiness self-assessments, document-readiness checklists, and similar planning fields stored with your savings plan.</li>
    <li><strong>Planning profile:</strong> information collected during onboarding (e.g., desired location).</li>
    <li><strong>Manual funding sources:</strong> names and amounts you enter when not using bank linking.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>3.2 From financial account linking (Plaid)</h3>
  <p>If you choose to connect accounts, <strong>Plaid Inc.</strong> collects credentials and communicates with your financial institution. We receive from Plaid (subject to your connection and Plaid’s terms) data such as:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Institution identifiers, names, branding metadata;</li>
    <li>Account identifiers, names, types;</li>
    <li>Balance and available amount fields used to display and refresh your home fund;</li>
    <li>Item identifiers needed to maintain the connection.</li>
  </ul>
